Voice-Based Concept Understanding Analyser (VBCUA)

Watch the demo here: [https://drive.google.com/file/d/1GCWwHgSZs-8_q5XDtvAvlCxQft1MQgw6/view?usp=drive_link]

An AI-powered web application that evaluates how effectively a user understands and explains
conceptual topics through spoken communication. It combines speech-to-text transcription,
semantic similarity analysis, audio feature extraction, and intelligent scoring to assess both
the quality of conceptual understanding and the fluency of speech delivery.

Built as part of the SmartBridge Generative AI internship (IBM SkillsBuild).


1. Project Overview

A student, trainer, or researcher uploads or records a spoken explanation of a concept (e.g.
"Machine Learning" or "Cloud Computing"). The system:


Transcribes the speech using OpenAI Whisper
Compares the explanation against a reference concept using Sentence-BERT semantic embeddings
Analyzes speech fluency — filler words, pauses, and voice energy — using NLTK and Librosa
Combines everything into a Similarity Score, Speech Score, and Final Score, with a
qualitative classification (Strong / Moderate / Poor Understanding)
Generates a downloadable PDF report with the transcript, scores, waveform, and feedback



2. Architecture

The application follows a three-layer architecture:

Presentation Layer (Streamlit Interface)
        ↓
Core Intelligence Layer
  ├── Speech-to-Text Module (Whisper)
  ├── Semantic Understanding Module (Sentence-BERT)
  ├── Filler Word Analysis Module (NLTK)
  ├── Audio Feature Extraction Module (Librosa)
  ├── Evaluation Scoring Module
  └── Report Generation Module (ReportLab)
        ↓
Supporting Data & AI Services Layer
  ├── Reference Concept Repository (JSON)
  ├── Sentence Embedding Models
  ├── Audio Processing Libraries
  └── SQLite Database

Page flow: Home → Upload Audio → Play Audio → Analyze → Result (transcript, scores,
waveform, feedback) → Download PDF Report


3. Features

#FeatureDetails1Audio UploadUpload .wav, .mp3, .m4a files2Audio PlaybackPlay back uploaded/recorded audio before analysis3Speech-to-TextWhisper transcribes speech to text, displayed in-app4Semantic AnalysisSentence-BERT compares the answer to a reference explanation, showing a similarity percentage5Filler Word DetectionNLTK-based detection of "um," "uh," "like," etc., with total count and ratio6Pause AnalysisTotal pauses and pause ratio, via Librosa silence detection7RMS Energy / ConfidenceVoice energy consistency mapped to a High/Medium/Low confidence label8Waveform VisualizationMatplotlib-rendered waveform of the recording9ScoringSimilarity Score, Speech Score, and Final Score (0–100)10FeedbackStrong / Moderate / Poor Understanding classification with actionable suggestions11PDF ReportDownloadable report with transcript, scores, waveform, and feedback12Session HistoryPast evaluations stored and viewable in a history table


